    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "rest. yeah. that's the word. it sounds so much better than \"moving on\" or \"searching.\" everyone keeps telling me to keep hiking, to find the next trail, but the thought of another mile just feels heavy. like i'm just dragging these bags around for no reason. if the story is finished, why do people insist on making you write more pages that don't even matter?",
